Contains the grammar definition

Each grammar declaration contains a list of rules and tokens.
  - Grammar declaration are [ruleName]
  - Rules are {ruleName}
  - Tokens are (tokenName)

What precedes each grammar line must be a tabbed list of lines expanding undefined rules (with no previous grammar declaration)
declared in the previous grammar line in the order they appear.

_____

formal grammar definition:
_____

[compilationUnit] → {compilationUnitItem} {compilationUnit} | END_OF_FILE
  [compilationUnitItem] → {globalVariableDeclaration} | {directive} | {function}
  
    [globalVariableDeclaration] → {type} (IDENTIFER) {initializer}
      [type] → {data} | {data} (AMPERSAND)
        [data] → (INT) | (SIGNED_INT_32) | (UNSIGNED_INT_32) | (BOOl) | (STRING) | (CHAR)    
      [initializer] → (EQUAL) {literal} (NEWLINE) | e
        [literal] → (STRING_LITERAL) | (INTEGER_LITERAL) 
    
    [directive] → (LEFT_BRACKET)(RIGHT_BRACKET) | e

    [function] → {type} (IDENTIFER) (LEFT_PARENTHESIS) {parametersDeclaration} (RIGHT_PARENTHESIS) {directive} {functionBody}
      [parametersDeclaration] → {parametersDeclarationList} | e
        [parametersDeclarationList] → {type} (IDENTIFER) | {type} (IDENTIFER) (COMMA) {parametersDeclaration}
      
      [functionBody] →  {block} | e
        [block] → (LEFT_CURLY_BRACE) {statement} {return} (RIGHT_CURLY_BRACE)
          [statement] → {variableDeclaration} {statement} | {assignment} {statement} | {controlflow} {statement} | {functionCall} {statement} | e
            [variableDeclaration] → {type} (IDENTIFER)
            [assignment] → {assignmentTarget} (EQUAL) {expression} (NEWLINE)
              [assignmentTarget] → {variableDeclaration} | {variableUsage}
                [variableUsage] → (IDENTIFER) | {pointerOperator} (IDENTIFER)
                  [pointerOperator] → (AMPERSAND) | (STAR)

              [expression] → {expression} {operator} {operand} | {operand} 
                [operand] → {variableUsage} | {literal} | {functionCall}       
                  [functionCall] → (IDENTIFER) (LEFT_PARENTHESIS) {parametersCall} (RIGHT_PARENTHESIS)
                    [parametersCall] → {parametersCallList} | e
                      [parametersCallList] → {expression} | {expression} (COMMA) {parametersCallList}
                [operator] → {arithmeticOperator} | {booleanOperator}
                  [arithmeticOperator] → (PLUS) | (MINUS)
                  [booleanOperator] → (AND) | (OR)

          [controlflow] → {conditionalBranch}
            [conditionalBranch] → (IF) {ifClause} {block} {continuedCondition}
              [ifClause] → (LEFT_PARENTHESIS) {expression} (RIGHT_PARENTHESIS)
              [continuedCondition] → (ELSE) {block} | (ELIF) {ifClause} {block} {continuedCondition} | e
          [return] → (RETURN) [expression] | e
        
_____

Token definition:
_____

(IDENTIFER) → [a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*

(IF) → if
(ELSE) → else
(ELIF) → elif
(AND) → and
(OR) → or
(RETURN) → return 

(LEFT_PARENTHESIS) → (
(RIGHT_PARENTHESIS) → )
(LEFT_CURLY_BRACE) → {
(RIGHT_CURLY_BRACE) → }
(LEFT_BRACKET) → [
(RIGHT_BRACKET) → ]
(COMMA) → ,
(NEWLINE) → \n | \r | \n\r

(INT) → int
(SIGNED_INT_32) → sint32
(UNSIGNED_INT_32) → uint32
(BOOL) → true | false
(STRING) → string
(CHAR) → char

(PLUS) → +
(MINUS) → -
(EQUAL) → =
(AMPERSAND) → &
(STAR) → *

(INTEGER_LITERAL) → [0-9]+
(STRING_LITERAL) → ".*"

(END_OF_FILE) → EOF